Create a styled gt table

Source: R/dta_gtable.R
dta_gtable.Rd

dta_gtable() creates a gt table from the input data frame and applies a consistent styling with vertical borders, bold column labels, reduced padding, and customized background colors.

Usage

dta_gtable(dat)

Arguments

dat

A data frame that you want to render and style as a gt table.

Value

A styled gt table object.

Examples

data("women")
dta_gtable(women)
